DetailedDescription:
The Unique learner number (

Learner.ULN


), must pass the checksum calculation

(error where DD01 = 'N' or (DD01 <> 'Y' and DD01 <> 10th digit of 

Learner.ULN


))

A learner must not have more than one LLDD and Health Problem record (

LLDDandHealthProblem.LLDDCat


) with the same LLDD and health problem category

(error where There is more than one record for the learner with the same 

LLDDandHealthProblem.LLDDCat


)

There must not be more than one Learner Funding and Monitoring (FAM) record with the same Learner FAM type (

LearnerFAM.LearnFAMType


) and Learner FAM code (

LearnerFAM.LearnFAMCode


)

(error where there is more than one record for the learner with the same combination of 

LearnerFAM.LearnFAMType 


and 

LearnerFAM.LearnFAMCode


)

A learning aim must not have Learning Delivery FAM records with overlapping dates of certain Learning Delivery FAM types (Learning Support Funding (LSF) or Advanced Learner Loans Bursary (ALB)). Each type is treated separately.  

(error where there is more than one occurrance of either  LearnDelFAMType = (LSF and ALB) and the corresponding  'Date to' (

LearningDeliveryFAM.LearnDelFAMDateTo


) of the earlier record is after the corresponding  'Date from' (

LearningDeliveryFAM.LearnDelFAMDateFrom


) of the later record).

The Subcontracted or partnership UKPRN (

LearningDelivery.PartnerUKPRN


), must not be the same as the lead provider's UKPRN (

LearningProvider.UKPRN


)

(error where 

LearningDelivery.PartnerUKPRN


 =

 LearningProvider.UKPRN


)

The Learning aim reference (

LearningDelivery.LearnAimRef


) must be a valid lookup on LARS

Exclusions:
This rule is not triggered by: Community learning aims (

LearningDelivery.FundModel


) = 10
None funded provision (

LearningDelivery.FundModel


)= 99
16-19 funded learners (

LearningDelivery.FundModel


)= 25 or 82
or Tailored Learning funded (

LearningDelivery.FundModel


) = 11

This rule is not triggered by learners aged 25 or over at start (DD06 - 

Learner.DateOfBirth


) >= 25 years)
